# Technical Specification: Response-Option Generation Module

**Document ID:** MS-ODNI-ATAP-ROS-001  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Classification:** TS/SCI with SAP Access  
**Project Reference:** ODNI Accelerated Threat Assessment Platform (Contract #HHM402-25-C-0018)  
**Phase:** Capability Expansion (Phase 2)  
**Status:** Draft for Client Review  

## 1. Module Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
The Response-Option Generation (ROG) module extends the existing NLP-based threat assessment pipeline to automatically generate advisory response-option packages for kinetic threats. This module processes identified threats (e.g., weapons facilities, hostile force concentrations, mobile launchers) and pre-computes strike packages as advisory outputs. Outputs are strictly advisory and require human validation by planning staff. The module integrates with existing data overlays (e.g., civilian population density) and leverages proportionality analysis to provide preliminary go/no-go recommendations.

Key benefits:
- Reduces planning staff workload by 6-8 hours per package.
- Ensures outputs are traceable, auditable, and compliant with client policy frameworks (e.g., DoD proportionality guidelines under LOAC).

### 1.2 Scope
- **In Scope:** Kinetic threats only; pre-computation of strike packages including coordinates, munitions recommendations, blast radius, collateral estimates, and proportionality-based go/no-go.
- **Out of Scope:** Non-kinetic threats (e.g., cyber, EW); real-time execution; policy overrides; integration with live munitions systems (advisory only).
- **Assumptions:** Access to existing geospatial intelligence (GEOINT) feeds, munitions databases, and population density overlays is authorized. All outputs are flagged as "Advisory - Human Validation Required."

### 1.3 High-Level Requirements
- **Functional:** Generate packages for 95% of identified kinetic threats within 5 minutes of assessment completion.
- **Non-Functional:** 
  - Scalability: Handle up to 10,000 threats/day across 6 combatant commands.
  - Accuracy: Collateral estimates within ±10% margin (based on overlay data quality).
  - Security: All data processing at TS/SCI level; audit logging for all generations.
- **Compliance:** Outputs align with client-approved proportionality models (e.g., based on ICRC guidelines); no automated decision-making.

## 2. Data Models

### 2.1 Input Data Models
Inputs are derived from the existing NLP threat assessment pipeline.

- **Threat Entity Model** (JSON Schema):
  ```json
  {
    "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "threatId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique threat identifier" },
      "threatType": { "type": "string", "enum": ["weaponsFacility", "hostileForceConcentration", "mobileLauncher"] },
      "coordinates": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "latitude": { "type": "number" },
          "longitude": { "type": "number" },
          "accuracy": { "type": "number", "description": "In meters" }
        },
        "required": ["latitude", "longitude"]
      },
      "threatDescription": { "type": "string" },
      "assessmentTimestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" }
    },
    "required": ["threatId", "threatType", "coordinates"]
  }
  ```

- **Overlay Data Models** (Integrated from GEOINT feeds):
  - Civilian Population Density: Raster data (GeoTIFF) with population per km².
  - Terrain/Environmental: Vector data (GeoJSON) for urban/rural classification.

### 2.2 Output Data Models
- **Strike Package Model** (JSON Schema):
  ```json
  {
    "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "packageId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique package identifier" },
      "threatId": { "type": "string" },
      "targetCoordinates": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "latitude": { "type": "number" },
          "longitude": { "type": "number" }
        },
        "required": ["latitude", "longitude"]
      },
      "recommendedMunitions": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "munitionType": { "type": "string", "enum": ["JDAM", "Tomahawk", "Hellfire", "Other"] },
            "quantity": { "type": "integer" },
            "rationale": { "type": "string" }
          },
          "required": ["munitionType"]
        }
      },
      "expectedBlastRadius": { "type": "number", "description": "In meters" },
      "collateralDamageEstimate": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "civilianCasualtiesLow": { "type": "number" },
          "civilianCasualtiesHigh": { "type": "number" },
          "infrastructureImpact": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Low", "Medium", "High"] },
          "source": { "type": "string", "description": "Population density overlay reference" }
        },
        "required": ["civilianCasualtiesLow", "civilianCasualtiesHigh"]
      },
      "proportionalityRecommendation": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "goNoGo": { "type": "string", "enum": ["Go", "No-Go", "Conditional"] },
          "rationale": { "type": "string" },
          "confidence": { "type": "number", "minimum": 0, "maximum": 1 }
        },
        "required": ["goNoGo", "rationale"]
      },
      "generationTimestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
      "advisoryNote": { "type": "string", "default": "Advisory Only - Requires Human Validation" }
    },
    "required": ["packageId", "threatId", "targetCoordinates", "recommendedMunitions", "expectedBlastRadius", "collateralDamageEstimate", "proportionalityRecommendation"]
  }
  ```

## 3. API Contracts

### 3.1 Internal APIs (Microservices)
- **Endpoint:** `/generate-strike-package` (POST)  
  **Description:** Triggers package generation from threat assessment output.  
  **Request Body:** Threat Entity Model (JSON).  
  **Response:** Strike Package Model (JSON, 200 OK) or error (400/500).  
  **Authentication:** JWT with TS/SCI claims.  
  **Rate Limit:** 1000/min per node.

- **Endpoint:** `/validate-proportionality` (POST)  
